            <div type="apparatus"/>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>Κύριε βοήθει τῷ σῷ δούλῳ Ἰωάννῃ πρωτοσπαθαρίῳ ἐπὶ τοῦ Χρυσοτρικλίνου
                    κριτῇ τοῦ βήλου καὶ γηροτρόφῳ τῷ Χρυσοβέργῃ.</p>
                <p xml:lang="en">Lord, help your servant John Chrysoberges protospatharios, epi tou Chrysotriklinou,
                    krites of the Velon, and gerotrophos.</p>
                  <!--<p xml:lang="de">Notre seigneur Justinien, perpétuel auguste.</p>-->
              </div>
            <div type="commentary" subtype="text">
                <p>The owner of the seal, John Chrysoberges, is known from sigillographic
                    evidence, and his career can be reconstructed in the wake of the most recent
                    findings.[1] Two previous stages of his career can be inferred from two seals,
                    kept in the Archaeological Museum in Istanbul and at Dumbarton Oaks,
                    where he is attested as βασιλικὸς σπαθαροκανδιδάτος[2] and as σπαθαροκανδιδάτος,
                    πρωτοκαγκελλάριος τοῦ γενικοῦ, κριτής, ἀναγραφεύς and
                    κουράτωρ Μελιτηνῆς respectively.[3] Our specimen shows him at the highest
                    stage of his hitherto known career as προτοσπαθάριος, ἐπὶ τοῦ Χρυσοτρικλίνου,
                    κριτὴς τοῦ βήλου and γηροτρόφος. This means that John Chrysoberges
                    cumulates his high dignities and offices with that of γηροτρόφος, i.e.
                    director of a γηροτροφεῖον (or γηροκομεῖον), a home for the destitute elderly
                    set within the context of the charitable foundations (εὐαγεῖς οἶκοι)[4].</p>
              </div>
            <div type="commentary" subtype="footnotes">
                  <p xml:id="footnote-1">
                      [1]. See <ref target="http://pbw2016.kdl.kcl.ac.uk/person/Ioannes/20484/">PBW, Ioannes no. 20484</ref> = <ref target="https://www.degruyter.com/database/PMBZ/entry/PMBZ25534/html">PMBZ, no. 23380</ref>. The reading of the legend of the
                      seal mentioned in <ref target="https://pbw2016.kdl.kcl.ac.uk/boulloterion/3683/">PBW, Boulloterion no. 3683</ref>, Κύριε βοήθει τῷ σῷ δούλῳ Ἰωάννῃ πρωτοσπαθαρίῳ
                      ἐπὶ τοῦ Χρυσοτρικλίνου κριτῇ τοῦ βήλου γηροτρόφῳ τῷ Χρυσοβέργῃ τῷ Νικερίτῃ
                      is evidently incorrect; τῷ Νικερίτῃ was mistakenly added and ought to be expunged..
                  </p>
                <p xml:id="footnote-2">
                    [2]. <bibl><ptr target="Istanbul"/>, <citedRange unit="page">510, no. 5.223</citedRange></bibl>.
                  </p>
                <p xml:id="footnote-3">
                    [3]. Dumbarton Oaks BZS.1947.2.1066 (Shaw Collection), published in <bibl><ptr target="DOseals4"/>, <citedRange unit="page">159, no. 68.6</citedRange></bibl>.
                </p>
                <p xml:id="footnote-4">
                    [4]. On the office of the γηροτρόφος (or γηροκόμος), see <bibl><ptr target="Leontaritou1996"/>especially <citedRange unit="page">134-140</citedRange></bibl>. On the administration of the house for the elderly, see <bibl><ptr target="Constantelos1991"/>, especially <citedRange>222-240</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="Talbot1984"/>, especially <citedRange>275-278</citedRange></bibl>. For a
                    broad analysis of the administration of the charitable foundations in Byzantium, see <bibl><ptr target="Kaplan1976"/></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="Kaplan2006"/></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="Kaplan2006a"/></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="Volk1983"/></bibl>. The office of the γηροκόμος will
                    be object of an in-depth investigation carried out by M. Filosa in her doctoral thesis focussing
                    on the administration of the charitable foundations in the light of lead seals.
                </p>
              </div>
